      "abstract": "of maximum degree \\(\\), there is an integer g(H) such that every finite graph of minimum degree n and girth at least g(H) contains a subdivision of H. This had been conjectured for \\(\\) in [8]. We prove also that every finite 2n-connected graph of sufficiently large girth is n-linked, and this is best possible for all \\(\\)."
